  "notes": [
    "Quadkeys are z=9 (~76km tiles). The prewarm script fetches each",
    "listed quadkey and writes it to the Modal volume so runtime",
    "lookups don't pay an Azure cold-fetch on first hit per address.",
    "",
    "REPLACED 2026-05-15: the prior Orlando/Tampa/Jacksonville/Panhandle",
    "entries shipped with quadkeys that mapped to tiles in Colombia/",
    "Venezuela (computed against a different tile convention than the",
    "Bing system used by the runtime). Every FL customer address was",
    "hitting no_coverage as a result. The fix unifies all of Florida",
    "into one statewide entry with 144 z=9 tiles, computed from",
    "lib/sources/ms-buildings.ts's latLngToQuadkey at zoom=9 against",
    "FL's state envelope (24.4-31.05 lat, -87.65 to -79.95 lng).",
    "",
    "TO RE-RUN: modal run scripts.prewarm_ms_buildings",
    "(Idempotent \u2014 already-prewarmed tiles at this release will skip.)",
    "Required: Modal credentials, MS_BUILDINGS_SERVICE_URL set in env.",
    "",
    "TO ADD ANOTHER STATE:",
    "  1. Compute z=9 quadkeys via lib/sources/ms-buildings.ts",
    "     latLngToQuadkey(lat, lng, 9) over a state envelope grid",
    "  2. Append a new metros[] entry with counties + bounds + quadkeys",
    "  3. Run prewarm + open PR"
  ]
}